summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2019 KEYSTONE ALPINE. THE CONTACT STATED WHILE DRIVING AT AN UNKNOWN SPEED, TWO LEVELING JACKS STARTED DESCENDING FROM THE TRAILER PREVENTING THE TRAILER FROM MOVING. THE CONTACT PULLED OVER TO THE SHOULDER BUT COULD NOT GET THE JACKS TO RETRACT AND STAY IN PLACE. THE TRAILER WAS TOWED TO THE CONTACT'S DESTINATION.  THE MANUFACTURER DISPATCHED A MOBILE SERVICE TECHNICIAN WITH REPLACEMENT JACKS BUT THE REMEDY FAILED. THE CONTACT THEN DISCONNECTED THE HYDRAULICS TO THE LEVELING JACKS AND WAS ABLE TO CONTINUE TO DRIVE AFTER TWO WEEKS OF ATTEMPTING TO REMEDY THE FAILURE. THE CONTACT SCHEDULED AN APPOINTMENT WITH THE DEALER CAMPING WORLD OF SPARTANBURG (114 BEST DR, SPARTANBURG, SC 29303, (866) 955-8753) FOR JANUARY 2019. THE MANUFACTURER HAS REIMBURSED THE CONTACT FOR EXPENSES BUT COULD NOT OFFER ANY FURTHER ASSISTANCE UNTIL THE FAILURE HAS BEEN DIAGNOSED BY THE DEALER. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 100 MILES.
